The worst thing about Christmas is having to buy presents for people. 

Presents are stupid.

If I want something, I just go and buy it. Then I know I'm getting the thing I actually want, not something that someone else thinks I want. Say for example, I ask for an electric screwdriver for Christmas. Someone will get me one, and it'll probably do the job. But it won't be the one I would have chosen. I would rather go to B&Q myself and look at their selection of electric screwdrivers, compare the specs, and feel the quality before deciding which one to get. Sure, I could figure out which one I want and tell my mum the specific model number, but what's the point? I'll know what it is before I unwrap it, and I could have bought it myself when I was in the shop.

I have no idea what anyone in my family would like for Christmas. I generally spend the entire month of December feeling stressed and sick because I know I need to buy presents but I don't know what to get. I know I'll end up getting shit presents that people don't want. It's the 1st of December today and the feeling of dread has already started.
